01:01.338 --> 01:03.640
Castle, down on the ground, now!

01:21.503 --> 01:23.421
Come on.

01:35.611 --> 01:38.879
Are you guys re-enacting
the humpty dumpty crime scene?

01:38.914 --> 01:41.482
It's the autumnal equinox
today.

01:41.516 --> 01:43.517
Yeah, and according
to Mr. Wizard there,

01:43.585 --> 01:45.720
it's the only time of year you
can balance an egg on its tip.

01:45.754 --> 01:46.889
Don't you guys have work to do?
Nah.

01:46.941 --> 01:49.576
No, not really.
Hmm. Well, now you do.

01:53.401 --> 01:55.403
By the way, that whole thing
with the egg

01:55.457 --> 01:57.258
is just urban legend.
Not true.

01:57.292 --> 01:59.927
I saw Castle do it
last year.

02:04.053 --> 02:06.604
What's wrong with you?

02:06.639 --> 02:08.639
Still no word from him?

02:08.674 --> 02:10.608
No.

02:12.178 --> 02:14.529
Maybe you should call him.

02:14.563 --> 02:16.381
He said that he would
be back the fall,

02:16.403 --> 02:19.538
and it's fall, so clearly,
he has better things to do.

02:20.190 --> 02:22.090
Maybe he's not back
from the Hamptons yet.

02:22.125 --> 02:23.026
Maybe he's still working
on his book.

02:28.895 --> 02:32.297
Beckett.

02:32.332 --> 02:33.932
Yeah.

02:36.035 --> 02:37.953
I need you people
to move back, please.

02:37.987 --> 02:39.421
Ma'am, please get back.

02:42.392 --> 02:44.910
Ooh.
Speaking of humpty dumpty.

02:44.944 --> 02:48.030
Maybe somebody tried
to stand her up on her head.

02:48.064 --> 02:50.582
After all, it is
the autumnal equinox.

02:50.616 --> 02:53.101
It wasn't the fall
that killed her.

02:53.136 --> 02:55.053
More like multiple
gunshot wounds to the torso

02:55.087 --> 02:58.056
before doing a Greg Louganis
out that window up there.

02:58.396 --> 03:00.497
Victim's name is Chloe Whitman.
Couple of pedestrians

03:00.531 --> 03:02.866
heard shots and saw the body
fall out the window,

03:02.915 --> 03:04.816
but when uniforms got here,
the apartment was empty.

03:04.834 --> 03:07.235
There's no doorman on duty,
so, so far, no one recalls

03:07.270 --> 03:08.754
seeing anyone flee the scene.

03:09.587 --> 03:11.471
All right, have uniforms
start knocking on doors.

03:11.522 --> 03:14.257
Find out what else
our neighbors didn't see.

03:14.292 --> 03:17.260
Hey, it's Castle.

03:28.540 --> 03:30.642
Guess he did
finish that book.

03:33.112 --> 03:36.481
Nice of him
to send us a copy.

03:38.284 --> 03:40.301
It looks like
he's back in town.

03:40.336 --> 03:41.853
Nice of him to call.

03:41.887 --> 03:43.906
All right, guys. You can stop
pining for your girlfriend.

03:43.911 --> 03:46.012
After all, we got a body
full of holes.

03:46.046 --> 03:47.248
So what else do we know
about our victim?

03:47.558 --> 03:49.258
She's got a boyfriend.
Evan Murphy. He's on his way.

03:50.628 --> 03:55.064
Okay, let's go upstairs
and see what else we can find.

04:08.112 --> 04:10.046
He really is ruggedly handsome.

04:10.080 --> 04:11.331
Mm.

04:13.604 --> 04:16.140
From the spatter pattern, she
was backing away from the door.

04:16.214 --> 04:18.450
After the first bullet hits her,
she tries to get away.

04:18.483 --> 04:20.752
Got nowhere to go
but out the window.

04:20.786 --> 04:22.287
So large caliber gun.

04:22.321 --> 04:24.890
Round goes through her
and breaks the glass.

04:24.924 --> 04:26.341
She goes diving out.

04:28.894 --> 04:31.096
Looks like
she was leaving town.

04:37.020 --> 04:38.788
Well, it wasn't a robbery.

04:38.808 --> 04:40.709
Would you check these items
for fibers and prints?

04:40.743 --> 04:41.978
If we're lucky,
there was a struggle.

04:41.988 --> 04:43.188
Sure. We'll take care of it.

04:43.215 --> 04:46.550
Beckett,
Chloe's boyfriend Evan is here.

04:48.003 --> 04:51.655
So someone just came here
and shot her for no reason?

04:51.690 --> 04:54.558
Well, usually, in cases
like these, there is a reason.

04:54.593 --> 04:57.561
How long had you
and Ms. Whitman been dating?

04:59.151 --> 05:00.885
About six months.

05:00.919 --> 05:03.221
And was there anyone in her life
with violent tendencies,

05:03.247 --> 05:05.515
maybe anyone that
she had disputes with?

05:05.550 --> 05:07.117
No. No, she...

05:07.151 --> 05:10.921
The worst thing I ever
saw her do was jaywalk.

05:10.955 --> 05:13.640
What did she do for a living?
She's a teacher.

05:13.691 --> 05:16.059
She was a teacher.

05:16.906 --> 05:18.339
They all loved her.

05:18.374 --> 05:20.375
Were you
expecting her over tonight?

05:20.409 --> 05:23.611
No. Why?
Well, she packed an overnight bag.

05:23.646 --> 05:26.347
That--
that doesn't make sense.

05:26.382 --> 05:27.799
She--she has class tomorrow.

05:27.850 --> 05:31.069
She wouldn't just leave
without saying anything.

05:32.371 --> 05:33.955
Excuse me.

05:36.892 --> 05:40.127
Victim had it in her hand.
It was in her fingers so tight,

05:40.240 --> 05:41.774
I almost didn't see it.

05:41.799 --> 05:44.785
This is an address in Tribeca.
Could be where she was going.

05:44.819 --> 05:46.719
Only one way to find out.

05:47.971 --> 05:50.223
The address is registered
to a Maya Santori.

05:50.261 --> 05:51.878
32. She's clean.
No priors.

05:51.912 --> 05:53.480
417?
Yeah.

05:53.514 --> 05:55.151
Yeah, right there.

05:56.584 --> 05:58.268
It's open.

06:30.053 --> 06:32.287
NYPD!
NYPD! Let me see your hands.

06:32.322 --> 06:33.889
Drop it, now!
Gun!

06:33.923 --> 06:35.890
No!

06:35.908 --> 06:37.576
Whoa!

06:37.610 --> 06:38.660
Castle?

06:38.695 --> 06:40.362
Beckett?

06:40.396 --> 06:42.397
What are you doing here?

06:42.432 --> 06:43.966
I... uh...

06:44.003 --> 06:45.837
Down! Down!
Put it down!

06:45.871 --> 06:48.256
Drop that gun now!
Drop the gun, stupid!
Drop the gun!

06:48.290 --> 06:50.375
Yeah, no, no, it's okay.
Drop it, slimebag!

06:50.426 --> 06:52.677
Whoa. Okay, guys, easy.
It's not what it looks like.

06:52.711 --> 06:55.830
It never is. Turn around.

06:55.864 --> 06:57.715
Castle, turn around.

06:57.766 --> 07:00.435
Richard Castle,
you're under arrest for murder.

