07:15.909 --> 07:17.194
Something's different.

07:17.248 --> 07:19.383
Did you remodel?

07:24.656 --> 07:27.624
You've been informed
of your rights, Mr. Castle?

07:27.659 --> 07:29.226
Really?

07:29.260 --> 07:31.728
You're not even gonna ask me
how my summer was?

07:31.763 --> 07:34.297
You are aware that you're
under arrest for murder?

07:34.332 --> 07:37.868
I thought you were being rough
with the cuffs just for fun.

07:37.902 --> 07:39.469
You look good.

07:39.504 --> 07:41.571
You look good, too.

07:41.606 --> 07:42.639
Yeah?

07:42.674 --> 07:44.875
For murder.
Why are you so mad at me?

07:44.970 --> 07:46.921
Maybe because you were found
standing over a dead body

07:46.972 --> 07:48.706
with a gun in your hand.

07:48.774 --> 07:50.192
Yeah, but I told you,
she was dead when I got there.

07:50.392 --> 07:52.443
Why didn't you call?

07:55.247 --> 07:58.983
I was going to call you.

07:59.017 --> 08:01.552
But then you showed up
before I could.

08:02.748 --> 08:05.516
Really?

08:04.312 --> 08:07.614
Well, then why did we find you
in our victim's apartment?

08:07.649 --> 08:09.116
Well, because she called me.

08:09.150 --> 08:12.019
Oh, so you and Ms. Santori
were in a relationship.

08:12.253 --> 08:13.688
Well, I wouldn't say
it was a relationship.

08:13.746 --> 08:14.615
I bought a couple
of sculptures from her.

08:14.625 --> 08:15.825
Were you sleeping with her?

08:17.001 --> 08:18.752
How is that relevant?
Motive.

08:18.786 --> 08:20.236
Ah.

08:20.254 --> 08:23.073
No, I wasn't
sleeping with her.

08:23.107 --> 08:25.041
Are you sure?
Beautiful woman--

08:25.076 --> 08:27.110
I'm in a relationship.
With whom?

08:27.144 --> 08:28.946
Is that a new lipstick?
Castle.

08:28.993 --> 08:29.795
You know with whom.

08:29.805 --> 08:31.605
How should I know?
I haven't seen you in months.

08:31.729 --> 08:33.697
You could've been
in dozens of relationships

08:33.731 --> 08:35.832
with women since then.
You sound jealous.

08:35.866 --> 08:37.884
Jealous of you dating your
second ex-wife and publisher?

08:38.904 --> 08:41.873
Tell me, does she make you
do <i>everything</i> on a deadline?

08:41.907 --> 08:43.375
So how about you?

08:43.409 --> 08:45.577
You still with that,
uh, cop boyfriend of yours?

08:45.611 --> 08:47.612
What was his name again--
Demming?

08:50.149 --> 08:51.649
You broke up?

08:51.667 --> 08:54.786
This victim that called you,
what was it about?

08:54.820 --> 08:56.088
She said she was in trouble

08:56.149 --> 08:57.285
and she couldn't go
to the police.

08:57.295 --> 08:59.115
So why did she call you?

08:59.704 --> 09:04.007
Because Maya knew I had
a relationship with you--ooh.

09:04.042 --> 09:05.075
With the NYPD.

09:05.168 --> 09:07.236
She thought I could help.
Help how?

09:07.270 --> 09:09.738
Well, she didn't say.
She just told me to come over.

09:09.772 --> 09:12.241
When I got the, the door
was open. The place was trashed.

09:13.100 --> 09:13.934
She was dead on the bed,

09:13.939 --> 09:15.907
and there was a gun
on the floor.

09:15.941 --> 09:18.743
So you, being the expert veteran
of dozens of crime scenes,

09:18.778 --> 09:20.745
decided to pick up
the murder weapon to,

09:20.780 --> 09:22.781
what, ensure that
we had your prints?

09:22.815 --> 09:25.750
Maybe you missed the part
where I said she was shot dead.

09:25.785 --> 09:27.602
When I heard the noises
coming from the next room,

09:27.653 --> 09:29.454
I thought whoever killed her
was coming back.

09:29.488 --> 09:31.456
So I picked up the gun
to defend myself.

09:31.490 --> 09:34.392
It seemed like a very good idea
at the time. That's when you,

09:34.410 --> 09:36.928
<i>Esposito and Annie Oakley come</i>
<i>bursting through the door.</i>

09:36.962 --> 09:39.364
Annie Oakley?
<i>Detective Esposito was responding--</i>

09:39.398 --> 09:42.700
<i>I am not a threat...</i>
I kinda almost shot Castle.

09:43.995 --> 09:45.162
What? He had a gun.

09:45.217 --> 09:46.601
Shoulda let you shoot him.

09:46.675 --> 09:47.993
It would've served him right
for not calling.

09:48.003 --> 09:49.103
<i>We should be</i>

09:49.128 --> 09:51.629
<i>at the crime scene</i>
<i>looking for clues.</i>

09:51.664 --> 09:54.699
<i>So tell me,</i>
<i>why should I believe you,</i>

09:54.733 --> 09:57.302
considering that you pretty much
make up stories for a living?

09:57.336 --> 09:58.903
Because you know me.

10:01.357 --> 10:03.358
Do you know her?
Chloe Whitman.

10:03.409 --> 10:05.109
She was shot to death.

10:05.144 --> 10:08.046
Your friend's address
was found in her hands

10:08.080 --> 10:09.681
after she was killed.

10:09.715 --> 10:11.816
Another murder?
What's their connection?

10:11.884 --> 10:14.985
I don't know. You were the one
with the gun. You tell me.

10:16.722 --> 10:18.106
Beckett, a word.

10:18.157 --> 10:20.958
Hey, Captain.
How's it going?

10:20.993 --> 10:22.610
What? You, too?

10:22.645 --> 10:23.778
Real--

10:23.829 --> 10:25.996
come on, guys.

10:27.332 --> 10:28.966
C.S.U. recovered the slugs

10:29.001 --> 10:31.102
from Maya Santori
and Chloe Whitman's place.

10:31.933 --> 10:34.869
The gun was a .45.
Castle was holding a .38.

10:34.903 --> 10:38.022
So it must have belonged
to the victim for self-defense,

10:38.066 --> 10:40.050
which means that Castle
was telling the truth.

10:40.084 --> 10:42.903
But I'd be happy to hold him
if you like.

10:44.750 --> 10:46.084
You're free to go.

10:46.176 --> 10:47.176
Well, that's it?

10:47.250 --> 10:50.486
Bullets don't match your gun.
You're off the hook.

10:50.520 --> 10:52.855
I'm--ooh!

10:52.873 --> 10:54.356
So what's our next move?

10:54.374 --> 10:56.342
There isn't one,
at least not for you.

10:56.376 --> 10:58.344
You're going home.
Whoa, whoa, whoa

10:58.378 --> 11:00.030
two victims, one of 'em
an acquaintance of mine,

11:00.076 --> 11:00.845
and you're sending me home?

11:00.855 --> 11:03.355
You're a witness, Castle.
I can't have you involved.

11:03.376 --> 11:06.377
I'm already involved.
Castle, go home.

11:07.006 --> 11:10.141
Go back to your Hamptons,
your ex-wife,

11:10.176 --> 11:11.593
your book parties.

11:11.644 --> 11:15.513
Okay? I've got work to do.

11:15.548 --> 11:17.748
What did I do?

11:30.230 --> 11:32.064
Darling!

11:32.115 --> 11:34.984
Hello! Oh,
you must see this video.

11:35.018 --> 11:38.020
It's absolutely...
Charming.

11:38.055 --> 11:40.723
A penguin smacks another penguin
into an ice hole.

11:40.757 --> 11:42.224
I'll show you.

11:42.242 --> 11:43.726
Ah, maybe later.

11:43.760 --> 11:47.563
Oh, you look as if someone
smacked you into an ice hole.

11:49.124 --> 11:51.625
I stopped by the precinct.

11:51.653 --> 11:53.588
I thought you weren't going back
till after the book tour.

11:53.674 --> 11:55.275
Yeah, well, fate intervened.

11:55.309 --> 11:57.677
Someone I know was murdered today.
Oh, lord.

11:57.711 --> 11:59.345
Dad, that's awful. Who?

11:59.380 --> 12:01.781
Maya. The woman who made
that sculpture for me.

12:01.816 --> 12:05.351
Any leads?
No, not yet.

12:05.386 --> 12:07.487
So how is everyone?

12:07.521 --> 12:10.023
Beckett have
a nice summer?

12:10.057 --> 12:11.858
Yeah, everyone's fine.

12:13.381 --> 12:15.049
Now why don't I believe you?

12:15.066 --> 12:17.067
Aren't you with Chet
on Tuesdays?

12:17.101 --> 12:19.002
Oh! That was never
set in stone.

12:19.036 --> 12:20.970
Besides,
Alexis is in crisis.

12:21.005 --> 12:23.423
The young man
from the summer program

12:23.457 --> 12:25.925
still hasn't called her.
Despite the fact he said we'd talk

12:25.976 --> 12:27.978
when he got back from Europe,
which he already did.

12:28.022 --> 12:29.757
Well, if you knew he was back,
why don't you just call him?

12:29.767 --> 12:31.267
He's the one who went away.

12:31.346 --> 12:32.748
I mean, if he still cared,
he would've called.

12:32.758 --> 12:34.578
Maybe he was going to,
but he didn't know

12:34.283 --> 12:36.350
how you'd feel about it.
Maybe he was worried

12:36.385 --> 12:39.103
that something had changed
while he was away.

12:39.154 --> 12:40.921
Oh, Richard Castle,

12:40.956 --> 12:42.890
that is the stupidest thing
I ever heard.

12:42.924 --> 12:45.192
Have I taught you nothing
about relationships?

12:45.226 --> 12:48.696
You're a shining example. Just
how big a deal is this anyway?

12:51.394 --> 12:53.446
I don't know if I even
want to see him anymore.

12:53.454 --> 12:55.222
Oh, come on. You're not even
giving him a chance.

12:55.239 --> 12:56.590
Why are you siding with him?

12:56.660 --> 13:00.828
I'm not. I ju--
maybe he'll do something

13:00.979 --> 13:01.980
that will make it right.

13:01.992 --> 13:05.361
Maybe he'll just--
maybe he'll surprise you.

13:05.395 --> 13:07.930
Maybe he missed his chance.

13:27.407 --> 13:30.309
If you ask me, you shoulda
locked him up just outta spite.

13:30.343 --> 13:32.744
No, that'd be unethical...

13:32.779 --> 13:35.013
Making the people down
in holding deal with him.

13:35.048 --> 13:36.431
True.

13:36.482 --> 13:38.116
Hey. Whoa.

13:38.151 --> 13:39.868
So... ballistics ran
a comparison

13:39.919 --> 13:41.837
of the slugs
from the two murders.

13:41.888 --> 13:43.488
They're from the same gun.

13:43.523 --> 13:45.357
Anything on the canvass?

13:45.375 --> 13:47.392
Well, we showed Chloe's photos
to Maya's friends and neighbors.

13:47.393 --> 13:49.594
They don't recognize her.
And Chloe's boyfriend

13:49.629 --> 13:50.930
and her colleagues
from her prep school,

13:50.948 --> 13:53.499
they don't know Maya either.

14:04.059 --> 14:06.960
Okay, so we've got...

14:06.995 --> 14:08.929
A High School
chemistry teacher

14:08.947 --> 14:10.397
and a sculptor

14:10.431 --> 14:12.399
who live on
two different sides of town

14:12.434 --> 14:15.469
and by all accounts, run in
completely different circles.

14:15.503 --> 14:17.438
They're both killed
on the same day

14:17.472 --> 14:20.174
and by the same person.

14:20.208 --> 14:24.194
There lives
must intersect somehow.

14:24.229 --> 14:26.113
All right,
run phones and financials.

14:26.147 --> 14:28.082
Let's see if anything pops.

14:28.116 --> 14:30.417
On it.

14:37.811 --> 14:41.380
I'm gonna go and see Lanie
and see if she's found anything.

14:44.250 --> 14:46.184
Ryan!

14:48.805 --> 14:49.955
Hey, L.T.

14:49.993 --> 14:51.961
Hey, Castle.
Back on the beat.

14:51.979 --> 14:54.430
Yeah, looking that way.
Is, uh, Beckett here?

14:54.448 --> 14:56.399
Finished her sweep
about an hour ago.

14:56.417 --> 14:57.867
Did she find anything?

14:57.902 --> 14:59.986
Nothing useful.

15:00.020 --> 15:01.971
Mind if I take
a look around?

15:25.138 --> 15:26.272
Hey, brother.

15:26.329 --> 15:28.796
Yeah.
Looks like you missed one.

15:28.815 --> 15:30.932
Okay.

15:36.272 --> 15:38.273
Hey.

15:38.307 --> 15:40.475
Hey I hear you made
an interesting arrest today.

15:40.510 --> 15:42.377
You want to talk about it?

15:42.411 --> 15:44.646
No.
Okay.

15:44.680 --> 15:46.898
Keep holding that stuff in.
You gon' get an ulcer.

15:46.933 --> 15:48.583
Anything unusual?

15:48.618 --> 15:50.252
You mean besides the gunshots?

15:50.286 --> 15:51.686
Yeah,
I'm looking for anything

15:51.721 --> 15:53.672
that will connect
these two victims.

15:53.723 --> 15:55.891
They both had tattoos.
Everyone has tattoos.

15:55.925 --> 15:58.093
Chloe Whitman, our jumper,

15:58.127 --> 15:59.611
has a Rose.

15:59.645 --> 16:02.764
