30:06.901 --> 30:08.703
"I know what you're doing.
I know all about it."

30:09.335 --> 30:12.037
I guess he thought she was
screwing someone else.

30:14.662 --> 30:17.564
Okay, so I followed Chloe
to the club that night,

30:17.599 --> 30:20.567
but only because she was
acting weird, secretive,

30:20.602 --> 30:22.636
and I thought she was seeing
another guy.

30:22.670 --> 30:24.755
Mr. Murphy, why didn't you
tell us this before?

30:24.806 --> 30:25.907
That I'd been fighting
with my girlfriend,

30:25.978 --> 30:28.079
that I'd threatened her?
I know how cops work.

30:29.201 --> 30:31.019
And when you found out
about the other victims,

30:31.070 --> 30:32.471
that they were all there at the club?
I didn't kill her.

30:32.553 --> 30:36.956
I didn't kill any of them.
What would you have done?

30:37.303 --> 30:39.137
I would try to help find
her killer.

30:39.172 --> 30:42.074
But if I had told you then
what you know now,

30:42.108 --> 30:44.176
would you have looked
any further than me?

30:44.210 --> 30:46.111
Mr. Murphy,
the money in Chloe's account,

30:46.145 --> 30:48.080
where did it come from?

30:49.667 --> 30:52.002
What money?

30:53.548 --> 30:56.317
So he admits to the fights
and the threats,

30:56.351 --> 30:57.820
but he claims not to know
anything about the money...

30:57.830 --> 30:59.530
Or how our victims
are connected

30:59.603 --> 31:01.537
other than the events
of that night.

31:01.571 --> 31:03.839
Do you believe him?
It doesn't matter what I believe.

31:03.907 --> 31:05.607
He's a viable suspect.
Hey, Ryan.

31:05.625 --> 31:09.345
I need you to get a search
warrant for Evan Murphy's place.

31:09.379 --> 31:11.180
And, Esposito, how are things
going over there?

31:11.214 --> 31:13.116
We ran the club's mailing list
for people with priors.

31:13.159 --> 31:14.827
These are the ones
that have popped so far.

31:16.680 --> 31:19.632
All right, run 'em for
any connections with our vics.
Right on.

31:21.396 --> 31:22.747
What?

31:22.823 --> 31:25.508
I've seen this guy's face.

31:32.166 --> 31:34.867
That's the same guy.

31:34.885 --> 31:37.370
Maya knew him.

31:37.405 --> 31:39.039
"Xander Doyle."

31:39.073 --> 31:41.274
Weapons charges,
conspiracy to distribute,

31:41.308 --> 31:44.144
and apparently,
he lives in the Bowery.

31:44.178 --> 31:47.080
How much you want to bet
Maya was on her way to see him

31:47.114 --> 31:48.965
after McCutchin's murder?

31:49.000 --> 31:50.450
Yeah, sure. I knew Maya.

31:50.468 --> 31:52.419
I met her at the club
a few months back.

31:52.453 --> 31:55.388
And what was
the nature of your relationship?

31:55.422 --> 31:57.741
She said she liked
the way I looked.

31:57.775 --> 31:59.192
You know how it goes.

31:59.226 --> 32:01.294
When was the last time
you saw her?

32:03.611 --> 32:05.746
Mr. Doyle, we have evidence
that indicates

32:05.764 --> 32:08.198
that Maya came to see you
the day she died.

32:08.233 --> 32:10.218
Look, she said she was
in trouble. She needed my help.

32:10.228 --> 32:11.548
What kind of trouble?

32:12.242 --> 32:14.176
She wouldn't say.

32:14.210 --> 32:16.161
Someone must have been
after her.

32:16.212 --> 32:18.130
And why would you say that?

32:18.181 --> 32:20.115
'Cause the reason
she came to see me is,

32:20.150 --> 32:21.717
she wanted to borrow a gun.

32:21.760 --> 32:23.660
That's why she was armed.

32:23.695 --> 32:25.446
She saw what happened to McCutchin.
She figured she'd be next.

32:25.508 --> 32:28.310
Mr. Doyle, did Maya give you
any indication

32:28.361 --> 32:30.763
as to what she might have
been involved in?

32:30.797 --> 32:32.765
No.
If I was a betting man...

32:34.398 --> 32:37.000
I ran into Maya
a few weeks ago on the street.

32:37.010 --> 32:39.978
She gave me a hug.
I could smell it.

32:40.013 --> 32:41.047
You could smell what?

32:41.059 --> 32:43.660
That sick smell--paint thinner,
acetone, bleach.

32:44.925 --> 32:47.693
I got a buddy who smells like
that. You know what he does?

32:47.728 --> 32:50.763
He makes meth.

32:51.901 --> 32:53.169
It's so obvious.

32:53.211 --> 32:55.479
I can't believe I didn't
think of it sooner.

32:55.513 --> 32:57.481
Do you really think
it was meth?

32:57.516 --> 32:59.033
It's the only thing
that makes any sense.

32:59.086 --> 33:01.003
All of our victims
were struggling financially.

33:01.037 --> 33:03.472
One night after the club closes,
they're all together

33:03.506 --> 33:05.474
talking about their money woes

33:05.526 --> 33:07.927
until our High School
chemistry teacher cracks a smile

33:07.961 --> 33:09.946
and says, "well, we could
always make meth."

33:09.980 --> 33:11.414
But the others don't laugh.

33:11.448 --> 33:13.916
They say,
"yeah, we could make meth."

33:15.371 --> 33:18.122
Just like that cable show.

33:18.173 --> 33:20.575
I'm telling you, it's drugs.

33:20.609 --> 33:22.877
It's not drugs.
Are you sure?

33:22.911 --> 33:25.246
Yes, and your guy was right
about the chemicals.

33:25.280 --> 33:27.181
I found trace amounts
of bleach, acetone,

33:27.216 --> 33:30.184
sodium chloride and ammonia
on all three bodies.

33:30.219 --> 33:33.187
So how can you tell it's not drugs?
Because of what's missing.

33:33.222 --> 33:35.123
If your guys
had been cooking up meth

33:35.157 --> 33:36.424
or any other street-lab drugs,

33:36.459 --> 33:38.160
there would be
other substances present,

33:38.263 --> 33:40.731
not to mention the trace amounts
of the finished product.

33:40.765 --> 33:43.467
That being said, they definitely
were up to something.

33:43.501 --> 33:44.802
Hmm.

33:45.797 --> 33:47.398
Beckett.
Hey, it's Ryan.

33:47.432 --> 33:49.333
That search warrant on
Evan Murphy's place?

33:49.367 --> 33:50.801
It paid off.

33:50.835 --> 33:53.103
We found the murder weapon.

33:53.138 --> 33:55.674
I swear to God, I've never seen
that before in my life.

33:55.684 --> 33:57.184
Then what was it doing
in your place?

33:57.233 --> 33:58.101
I don't know!

33:58.111 --> 33:59.911
What really happened the night
that you followed Chloe

34:00.001 --> 34:01.769
to the club?
I told you, we fought.

34:01.805 --> 34:04.290
About what?
And do not say the affair.

34:04.344 --> 34:07.695
What were the four of you into?
Evan, what's the connection?

34:07.988 --> 34:09.922
Why did you kill them?

34:09.956 --> 34:13.126
I want a lawyer. I'm not saying
anything else without a lawyer.

34:17.067 --> 34:19.268
P.D.'s office has been notified.
They're sending someone over.

34:19.317 --> 34:21.485
Okay, notify the D.A.
Maybe they can cut us a deal

34:21.495 --> 34:24.297
and help us figure out
what was really going on.

34:31.225 --> 34:32.476
I know that look.

34:32.478 --> 34:33.911
What look?

34:33.929 --> 34:37.483
That "something doesn't add up"
look.

34:37.516 --> 34:40.485
It's just the lab report
on the murder weapon.

34:40.520 --> 34:42.521
What about it?

34:42.556 --> 34:44.373
They didn't find
any fingerprints.

34:44.407 --> 34:45.792
He probably wiped it down.

34:45.833 --> 34:48.703
Why would he wipe it down
if he was gonna hang on to it?

34:48.737 --> 34:51.539
Maybe he was going to ditch it
but didn't get around to it.
Mm.

34:51.572 --> 34:53.942
Ditching it would be the first
thing that he would do.

34:53.952 --> 34:55.351
Maybe he thought
he still needed it.

34:55.489 --> 34:57.691
To kill someone else?
Or protect himself.

34:59.660 --> 35:00.661
Hey, yo, Beckett.

35:00.682 --> 35:02.617
Financials came back
on your boy Evan.

35:02.651 --> 35:05.853
There's no unusual activity.
Maybe that was his motive.

35:05.887 --> 35:08.855
Whatever it was they were up to,
he didn't get his cut.

35:08.942 --> 35:11.527
But what was his cut? I mean,
what the hell were they into?

35:11.578 --> 35:13.462
It's like a bad joke--
a sculptor,

35:13.496 --> 35:15.447
a vending machine salesman
and a chemistry teacher

35:15.465 --> 35:17.149
walk into a burlesque bar.

35:17.183 --> 35:19.285
Yeah, only we don't
have a punch line.

35:19.313 --> 35:22.516
Other than they made a bunch of
money and got themselves killed.

35:24.203 --> 35:25.870
"Made a bunch of money."

35:25.905 --> 35:27.505
What?

35:27.540 --> 35:30.842
A sculptor who works
with metal, a chemist...

35:30.876 --> 35:33.345
And a vending machine
operator...

35:33.379 --> 35:36.314
I think I know
what our victims were up to.

35:36.349 --> 35:38.750
Do we still have
Chloe's purse?

35:43.172 --> 35:44.689
Whoa.

35:49.595 --> 35:52.263
What are you looking for?

35:53.799 --> 35:55.433
Aha!

35:57.233 --> 35:58.319
Take a look
at the serial numbers

35:58.362 --> 36:00.279
on those bills.

36:09.581 --> 36:10.349
They're the same.

36:10.384 --> 36:12.253
These bills are all pre-1998.

36:12.263 --> 36:13.963
That's before
they redesigned the currency.

36:13.992 --> 36:16.877
That's our punch line. That's
how these people are connected.

36:16.928 --> 36:19.997
In counterfeiting, the hardest
thing to make is the paper.

36:20.031 --> 36:21.949
But they had all the paper
they needed.

36:22.000 --> 36:25.435
They had an unlimited supply of $1 Bills.
From the vending machines.

36:25.470 --> 36:27.571
And those chemicals we found
on our victims' bodies...

36:27.605 --> 36:29.539
Were used to whitewash
the singles

36:29.574 --> 36:31.375
in order to make
blank bank notes.

36:31.409 --> 36:34.044
A procedure requiring
the expertise of a chemist.

36:34.078 --> 36:37.446
And what do counterfeiters <i>do</i>
with blank bank notes?

36:37.720 --> 36:39.204
Print larger denominations,

36:39.238 --> 36:41.206
for which they need
a metal press plate.

36:41.240 --> 36:44.409
And who better to provide that
than a sculptor?

36:44.443 --> 36:46.377
So...

36:46.412 --> 36:49.881
Plates, paper...

36:49.915 --> 36:52.150
There's only
one missing ingredient.

36:52.184 --> 36:55.153
I know who the killer is!
I know who the killer is!

37:02.394 --> 37:05.447
Come on. Let's go.

37:18.404 --> 37:20.105
Come on! Hurry up!

37:26.931 --> 37:30.534
Get the plates! The plates!

37:34.138 --> 37:36.306
Going somewhere?

37:38.593 --> 37:40.644
Let me see your hands.

37:42.630 --> 37:45.782
Step away from the bags
and walk forward.

37:56.380 --> 37:57.582
Yeah, they're fake.

37:57.661 --> 37:59.261
What gave me away?

37:59.296 --> 38:00.963
The missing ingredient.

38:00.997 --> 38:04.433
Ink. And who better to
provide it than a tattoo artist?

38:04.467 --> 38:05.901
That and Evan Murphy.

38:05.935 --> 38:08.937
You knew that we'd follow up
after you told us that story,

38:08.972 --> 38:11.473
so you planted that gun, but you
just didn't have enough time

38:11.491 --> 38:13.442
to put his prints on it,
did you?

38:13.476 --> 38:15.344
Sweep the area--
look out!

38:15.378 --> 38:17.012
Oh!

38:19.699 --> 38:22.835
Go! Go! Get him!
Move! Move! Move!
Let's go! Let's go! Come on!

38:22.869 --> 38:24.787
He's over there!
Let's get him! Come on!

38:24.821 --> 38:27.489
Where's Kitty?
The money's gone.

38:28.674 --> 38:31.959
You stay here.
What if they come back?

38:52.064 --> 38:54.982
Hey! Hey!

39:01.240 --> 39:03.941
He's out here.
You got him?

39:03.976 --> 39:07.061
I think he went around
this way.

39:07.095 --> 39:10.348
Do you see him?
I don't see him.
I don't see him.

39:10.382 --> 39:12.550
Come on! Police!
Police!

39:12.584 --> 39:15.286
Show yourself. NYPD.
Come out.

39:35.841 --> 39:38.192
Castle,
down on the ground, now!

39:45.984 --> 39:47.818
Aah!
Aah! Oh-ohh-oh!

39:50.188 --> 39:51.622
Oh.

39:54.300 --> 39:55.667
Drop it. Drop it.

39:55.695 --> 39:58.530
Don't move.
Stay on the ground,
right where you are.

39:58.564 --> 40:02.667
Turn over. Stay where you are.
Don't touch the gun.

40:02.702 --> 40:04.335
Yeah.

40:05.821 --> 40:08.206
They hatched the plan
late one night at the club.

40:08.240 --> 40:10.642
They figured, victimless crime,
nobody would get hurt.

40:10.676 --> 40:12.911
Kitty and Earl would launder
the bills through the club

40:12.945 --> 40:14.846
and then make cash payments
to the others.

40:14.880 --> 40:16.781
It sounds like they had
a sweet deal going on.

40:16.816 --> 40:18.717
How'd it all go wrong?
Todd McCutchin.

40:18.751 --> 40:20.668
He was getting squeezed by
a loan shark, figured he'd try

40:20.703 --> 40:22.787
to make a payment
with counterfeit bills.

40:22.822 --> 40:24.756
The shark threatened
to rat him out

40:24.790 --> 40:26.025
unless he turned over
the operation.

40:26.227 --> 40:28.678
Maya and Chloe were willing,
but Kitty and Earl weren't.

40:29.600 --> 40:31.034
And when Todd confronted them,

40:31.069 --> 40:32.553
he had no idea
who he was dealing with.

40:32.604 --> 40:35.221
Kitty Canary,
A.K.A. Carla Breezer.

40:35.376 --> 40:37.393
She was a stripper in Seattle.

40:37.428 --> 40:39.312
She did a nickel
for a manslaughter charge

40:39.363 --> 40:41.297
for trying to run over
her boyfriend.

40:41.332 --> 40:43.699
When she got out, she got
a new name, new boyfriend

40:43.717 --> 40:45.668
and even changed coasts.

40:45.736 --> 40:48.171
She wasn't the type of girl
to let Todd take her down.

40:48.205 --> 40:49.639
They had everything
they needed--

40:49.657 --> 40:51.073
the chemical formulas,
the plates.

40:51.091 --> 40:53.443
All they had to do
was get rid of the others.

40:53.477 --> 40:55.378
Nice work, you two.
Very impressive.

40:55.412 --> 40:57.280
But tomorrow, I want you
to tell me the story

40:57.314 --> 40:59.682
about how Castle got your gun.

41:01.485 --> 41:05.655
So, uh...
I guess you won the bet.

41:05.689 --> 41:07.256
Yeah.

41:08.659 --> 41:11.110
But look, if you don't
want me to--

41:11.145 --> 41:14.731
no, no, no. No.
You won fair and square.

41:17.701 --> 41:20.003
So...

41:21.828 --> 41:23.896
See you tomorrow?

41:23.930 --> 41:26.064
See you tomorrow.

